                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.48B/505: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-22T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1924—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>172. Your 247, September 29, noon.</p>
                <p>Red Cross has deposited with the Department $466,140.88 for which you may draw a
                    draft the proceeds of which you may turn over to the appropriate Japanese
                    authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
